    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your<strong> roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
